{
  "text": "In the present study, we evaluated the feasibility of ICSI when applied to a very limited number of eggs. Our results show that infertile couples in whom the female partner requires donated oocytes and the male partner suffers from severe male factor infertility can achieve pregnancy by undergoing oocyte donation combined with the ICSI technique. The fertilization, embryo development and pregnancy rates approach the results of ICSI when used in couples with OTA and normal female partner [CITATION_1] .",
  "citation_candidates": [
